By Onyebuchi Ezigbo Nigeria recorded 1,430 new confirmed cases of Covid-19 on Monday. An update posted on the website of the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) said that on January 25, 2021, 1,430 new confirmed cases and three deaths were recorded in Nigeria. It said till date, 122,996 cases have been confirmed, while 98,359 cases have been discharged and 1,507 deaths recorded in 36 states and the Federal Capital Territory (FCT). The 1,430 new cases are reported from 19 states â€” Lagos (744), Plateau (100), Oyo (77), FCT (75), Nasarawa (74), Katsina (48), Edo (42), Kano (41), Enugu (37), Rivers (34), Ogun (33), Kwara (32), Niger (28), Ebonyi (27), Kaduna (26), Borno (12), Yobe (10), Ekiti (5), and Gombe (1).